article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 61, Long Beach St. 60
article.story: Long Beach, Calif. -- Josh Akognon's basket with 0.5 seconds remaining gave Cal State Fullerton a 61-60 victory over Long Beach State on Thursday night. Akognon, the ninth-leading scorer in the nation, made 11 of 23 shots and scored 31 points for the Titans (10-10, 4-4 Big West Conference). Stephan Gilling's 3-pointer gave the 49ers a 60-59 lead with 17 seconds left. Gilling made 6 of 11 shots and scored 15 points for Long Beach State (10-9, 5-2). Donovan Morris scored 10 points and T. J. Robinson had 15 rebounds for the 49ers, who remained in first place in the conference despite the loss. The 49ers were up 32-24 at halftime as the Titans shot only 29 percent (10-of-34) to the 49ers' 43 percent in the first half. Fullerton found the range in the second half and finished the game at 37 percent from the floor to Long Beach's 47 percent. The Titans had just 10 turnovers, five fewer than the 49ers, and outrebounded them 38-36.
